Default DEM from the floodam-ead package

floodam_ead_dem.Rd

This is the default DEM generated by the function generate_DEM located in the data-raw folder of the package source code, with default arguments.

Usage

floodam_ead_dem

Format

A PackedSpatRaster object, use 'terra::rast()' to unpack it.

Source

https://gitlab.irstea.fr/flood-appraisal/floodam/floodam-ead

Examples

data("floodam_ead_dem", package = "rsic2")
floodam_ead_dem
#> [1] "This is a PackedSpatRaster object. Use 'terra::unwrap()' to unpack it"
terra::rast(floodam_ead_dem)
#> class       : SpatRaster 
#> dimensions  : 400, 205, 1  (nrow, ncol, nlyr)

#> source(s)   : memory

#> max value   : 46.64037
